[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ex-internee Liam Shannon describes 1971 Army beatings

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Twelve men who were imprisoned without trial during Troubles in Northern Ireland have claimed new evidence has emerged that proves the UK government subjected them to torture.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
28 November 2013 Last updated at 17:19 GMT
Liam Shannon, one of the internees who became known as the Hooded Men, describes the interrogation techniques used against them over a week-long period in 1971.
